author: Krista Driscoll
title: Photo: Dusty Boot in Eagle hosts Pinktoberfest for Shaw Cancer Center
text: Expand Photo Special to the Daily | The Dusty Boot in Eagle will host its sixth-annual Pinktober Fest: Beer, Boobs, Brats from 4 p.m. to close Saturday, Oct. 10. For one evening, 20 percent of food and beverage sales at The Dusty Boot in Eagle will be donated to the Shaw Regional Cancer Center. There will also be a Win a Pair, Save a Pair raffle or live auction, with a chance to win a pair of beach cruiser bikes, sponsored by Mountain Beverage, or a pair of Icelantic skis, donated by Oskar Blues, plus swag giveaways and a stein-holding contest, with a German beer stein to the winner. Attendees can also take advantage of food and drink specials and listen to live music from local band Rewind from 5 to 8:30 p.m. Visit www.shawcancercenter.com and click on “Events & Outreach” and “Breast Cancer Awareness Month” to learn more. « » Related Media The Dusty Boot in Eagle will host its sixth-annual Pinktober Fest: Beer, Boobs, Brats from 4 p.m. to close Saturday, Oct. 10.
